      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Automobiles are better engineered than ever, and statistics indicate that those traveling in them have never been safer. So why is the average driving experience so bad? The answers: too much stress, too little civility and far too much traffic. With articles about curing highway phobia, keeping emotions in check and whether speed limits really work. SECTION H</p>
